WEBVTT

00:01:04.209 --> 00:01:06.211 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Grandpa!

00:01:06.211 --> 00:01:08.464 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Grandpa, what is this?

00:01:12.301 --> 00:01:14.303 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Where did you find this?

00:01:14.303 --> 00:01:16.305 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In the fields.

00:01:18.849 --> 00:01:20.851 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Come along.

00:01:20.851 --> 00:01:22.895 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I need to show you something.

00:01:22.895 --> 00:01:27.232 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I’ve never told you about my past, have I?

00:01:37.076 --> 00:01:39.995 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Josiah, you are still young now.

00:01:41.080 --> 00:01:44.166 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But one day you’ll learn more about my life.

00:01:45.584 --> 00:01:48.462 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I did many bad things.

00:01:51.090 --> 00:01:55.344 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I used to worship false gods instead of Jehovah.

00:01:57.054 --> 00:02:00.265 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I even brought idols into the temple.

00:02:02.142 --> 00:02:06.146 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I upset Jehovah very much.

00:02:10.275 --> 00:02:12.486 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And he disciplined me.

00:02:16.198 --> 00:02:20.661 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I begged Jehovah to forgive me.

00:02:20.661 --> 00:02:23.122 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Did he forgive you?

00:02:23.122 --> 00:02:26.875 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Yes. His mercy is great!

00:02:28.877 --> 00:02:33.716 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now, these are the words of Jehovah’s prophet Isaiah:

00:02:34.800 --> 00:02:37.052 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“All who form carved images

00:02:37.052 --> 00:02:39.221 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“amount to nothing,

00:02:39.221 --> 00:02:44.226 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and their cherished objects will be of no benefit.

00:02:45.185 --> 00:02:46.812 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“As their witnesses,

00:02:46.812 --> 00:02:49.982 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“they see nothing

00:02:49.982 --> 00:02:52.860 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and know nothing.”

00:02:53.694 --> 00:02:55.320 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now I want you to read

00:02:55.320 --> 00:03:00.117 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
these words down here about a man who cuts down a tree.

00:03:00.117 --> 00:03:02.828 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let’s see what he does with it.

00:03:02.828 --> 00:03:06.165 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Half of it he burns up in a fire;

00:03:06.165 --> 00:03:08.917 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“with that half

00:03:08.917 --> 00:03:13.130 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“he roasts the meat that he e-e-eats,

00:03:13.130 --> 00:03:17.259 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“and he is s-s-satisfied.

00:03:17.259 --> 00:03:21.305 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“He also warms himself and says:

00:03:21.305 --> 00:03:25.350 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘Ah! I am warm as I watch the fire.’”

00:03:25.350 --> 00:03:27.603 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Is that bad, Grandpa?

00:03:27.603 --> 00:03:29.021 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
No, my son.

00:03:29.021 --> 00:03:31.857 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But let’s see what he does with the other half.

00:03:34.735 --> 00:03:38.739 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“But the rest of it he makes into a god,

00:03:38.739 --> 00:03:43.243 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“into his c-c-carved image.

00:03:44.620 --> 00:03:49.625 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“He bows down to it and worships it.

00:03:50.417 --> 00:03:53.879 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“He prays to it and says:

00:03:53.879 --> 00:03:58.050 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
‘Save me, for you are my god.’”

00:03:58.050 --> 00:03:59.301 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
That’s wrong!

00:03:59.301 --> 00:04:02.888 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Why is it wrong, Josiah?

00:04:02.888 --> 00:04:04.890 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Because it’s not Jehovah.

00:04:04.890 --> 00:04:07.184 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It’s just a tree.

00:04:07.184 --> 00:04:09.853 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
How does Jehovah feel about doing something like that?

00:04:10.395 --> 00:04:13.482 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah doesn’t want us to serve any other gods?

00:04:13.482 --> 00:04:15.484 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Right.

00:04:15.484 --> 00:04:19.571 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Besides, can any other god listen to our prayers?

00:04:20.155 --> 00:04:22.991 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
No! Only Jehovah.

00:04:22.991 --> 00:04:27.412 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And Jehovah wants to hear your prayers, Josiah.

00:04:27.412 --> 00:04:30.499 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I always pray to him.

00:04:30.499 --> 00:04:33.669 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Pray to him many times a day

00:04:33.669 --> 00:04:35.671 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
from your heart.

00:04:35.671 --> 00:04:40.092 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
That shows you love him and want to be his friend.

00:04:41.093 --> 00:04:43.804 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
If you make a mistake,

00:04:43.804 --> 00:04:47.141 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
pray to Jehovah to forgive you.

00:04:47.141 --> 00:04:49.226 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Even for a hundred mistakes?

00:04:49.226 --> 00:04:51.311 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Even for a hundred.

00:04:51.311 --> 00:04:53.063 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
A thousand?

00:04:53.063 --> 00:04:54.064 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Yes.

00:04:54.690 --> 00:04:56.775 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
A thousand, thousand?

00:04:56.775 --> 00:05:01.572 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Even that many—if you pray to Jehovah to forgive you

00:05:01.572 --> 00:05:06.076 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and you really keep trying to do what is right.

00:05:15.502 --> 00:05:18.505 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Josiah, your grandfather needs to rest.

00:06:11.016 --> 00:06:13.018 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Finish telling me the story.

00:06:13.018 --> 00:06:14.686 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Where was I?

00:06:14.686 --> 00:06:16.688 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The angel.

00:06:16.688 --> 00:06:18.690 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Right.

00:06:18.690 --> 00:06:22.527 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Then Jehovah’s angel came down,

00:06:22.527 --> 00:06:25.197 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and whoosh!

00:06:27.699 --> 00:06:32.162 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
he destroyed 185,000 of Sennacherib’s troops.

00:06:32.162 --> 00:06:33.163 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Really?

00:06:33.163 --> 00:06:34.164 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Yes!

00:06:34.164 --> 00:06:36.166 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
King Hezekiah learned

00:06:36.166 --> 00:06:38.669 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that we can always trust in Jehovah.

00:06:38.669 --> 00:06:42.089 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I like going to the temple with you.

00:06:42.089 --> 00:06:44.341 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Zephaniah!

00:06:48.303 --> 00:06:50.722 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You shouldn’t fill the boy’s head with such stories.

00:06:50.722 --> 00:06:53.016 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The king told me to take Josiah to the temple.

00:06:53.016 --> 00:06:55.519 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I know where you’re going, and I don’t care what my father told you.

00:06:55.519 --> 00:06:56.520 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The boy isn’t—

00:06:56.520 --> 00:06:59.147 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Isn’t what?

00:06:59.147 --> 00:07:01.149 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Father, what are you doing out of bed?

00:07:01.149 --> 00:07:03.694 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Josiah wanted to go to the temple.

00:07:04.778 --> 00:07:07.155 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I had Zephaniah take him along ahead of me.

00:07:08.532 --> 00:07:11.451 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You may not want to join us,

00:07:11.451 --> 00:07:15.247 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but you will not prevent Josiah from going.

00:07:22.546 --> 00:07:24.172 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
As you wish.

00:07:38.312 --> 00:07:42.149 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Enan, this is a good one.

00:07:47.195 --> 00:07:49.197 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Who should I be this time?

00:07:50.574 --> 00:07:52.409 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I want to be King Solomon.

00:07:52.409 --> 00:07:54.453 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I was thinking I could be King David.

00:08:22.731 --> 00:08:23.940 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Quick!

00:08:25.275 --> 00:08:26.526 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Bring the boy!

00:08:26.526 --> 00:08:27.778 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
King Manasseh is asking for him!

00:08:29.363 --> 00:08:31.406 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Where is Josiah?

00:08:31.406 --> 00:08:33.408 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He’s on his way, my lord.

00:08:36.370 --> 00:08:38.413 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Grandfather!

00:08:38.413 --> 00:08:42.000 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Josiah,

00:08:42.000 --> 00:08:44.002 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
my son.

00:08:44.002 --> 00:08:46.129 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Listen to me.

00:08:48.090 --> 00:08:51.510 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Oh, Grandfather, you have to get better.

00:08:51.510 --> 00:08:53.512 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I’m afraid of being alone.

00:08:53.512 --> 00:08:55.514 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You’re not alone.

00:08:58.433 --> 00:09:00.435 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah is with you,

00:09:00.435 --> 00:09:05.107 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and so is your cousin Zephaniah.

00:09:05.107 --> 00:09:09.653 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah is holy,

00:09:09.653 --> 00:09:12.364 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and you must serve him

00:09:12.364 --> 00:09:14.533 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the way he wants us to

00:09:14.533 --> 00:09:18.036 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—and only that way.

00:09:20.747 --> 00:09:24.376 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The sacrifices and celebrations at the temple,

00:09:24.376 --> 00:09:29.005 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
they help us be friends with Jehovah.

00:09:29.798 --> 00:09:33.802 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I tried to restore pure worship,

00:09:36.680 --> 00:09:41.685 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but the people still sacrifice on the high places.

00:09:44.604 --> 00:09:49.609 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah’s temple—we’ve neglected it.

00:09:50.861 --> 00:09:55.115 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
How happy the people were when they worshipped

00:09:55.115 --> 00:09:58.869 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah the right way!

00:09:58.869 --> 00:10:03.373 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah’s temple and worship

00:10:03.373 --> 00:10:06.960 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
can be like that again.

00:10:12.174 --> 00:10:13.383 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Look at me.

00:10:15.802 --> 00:10:18.555 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Serve Jehovah, Josiah.

00:10:19.764 --> 00:10:23.185 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
All other gods

00:10:23.185 --> 00:10:25.228 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
are powerless.

00:10:57.886 --> 00:11:00.555 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I’m afraid of being alone.

00:11:08.146 --> 00:11:10.815 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You’re not alone.

00:11:14.986 --> 00:11:17.155 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah is with you.

00:12:01.491 --> 00:12:06.121 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
How happy the people were

00:12:06.121 --> 00:12:10.667 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
when they worshipped Jehovah the right way!

00:12:14.713 --> 00:12:17.549 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah’s temple

00:12:17.549 --> 00:12:19.551 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and worship

00:12:19.551 --> 00:12:22.554 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
can be like that again.

00:12:31.521 --> 00:12:33.315 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Josiah!

00:12:49.080 --> 00:12:51.750 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Father, that hurts!

00:13:08.391 --> 00:13:10.393 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
How is business?

00:13:10.393 --> 00:13:13.063 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The Phoenician models are beautiful,

00:13:13.063 --> 00:13:15.065 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and they’re selling briskly, Ben-Mattan.

00:13:15.065 --> 00:13:17.734 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Excellent! We’re making a bigger profit on them too.

00:13:18.443 --> 00:13:22.238 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They will bring blessings from Baal.

00:13:24.449 --> 00:13:26.576 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I can see the crops flourishing already.

00:13:27.827 --> 00:13:29.454 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah doesn’t like this.

00:13:30.747 --> 00:13:32.666 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Stop it!

00:13:35.293 --> 00:13:38.588 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We need the help of all the gods,

00:13:38.588 --> 00:13:40.298 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
not just Jehovah.

00:13:40.298 --> 00:13:43.343 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
That’s not what Grandfather taught me.

00:13:43.343 --> 00:13:46.054 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He said, “All other gods are powerless.”

00:13:46.054 --> 00:13:48.390 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Lower your voice.

00:13:48.390 --> 00:13:51.059 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Your grandfather knew Topheth better than anyone.

00:13:59.526 --> 00:14:04.114 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You, my son, can become a mighty man with Jehovah’s help

00:14:04.114 --> 00:14:06.408 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and Baal’s.

00:14:06.408 --> 00:14:07.617 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
That’s not right;

00:14:09.327 --> 00:14:12.330 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that’s not right.

00:14:12.330 --> 00:14:13.915 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
If we’re going to worship Jehovah,

00:14:13.915 --> 00:14:15.583 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
then we need to go to the temple.

00:14:15.583 --> 00:14:16.501 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Grandfather said that—

00:14:16.501 --> 00:14:19.212 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Never mind what your grandfather said!

00:14:20.588 --> 00:14:24.300 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He’s been dead for two years.

00:14:24.300 --> 00:14:28.471 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You are not to speak of him again. Understand?

00:14:30.014 --> 00:14:31.141 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Zephaniah!

00:14:56.916 --> 00:14:59.127 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Enan, let’s get out of here.

00:15:01.713 --> 00:15:03.131 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Enan.

00:15:11.097 --> 00:15:12.515 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
No!

00:15:13.558 --> 00:15:14.559 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
King Amon.

00:15:30.408 --> 00:15:31.409 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Josiah.

00:15:44.422 --> 00:15:45.507 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Take it.

00:15:45.507 --> 00:15:47.926 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Don’t make a scene.

00:15:47.926 --> 00:15:50.678 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
All other gods are powerless!

00:15:54.432 --> 00:15:56.476 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Agh! Let me go!

00:15:58.895 --> 00:16:00.355 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Not here!

00:16:00.355 --> 00:16:02.357 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Not standing before Baal!

00:16:03.066 --> 00:16:04.317 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Not—

00:16:26.256 --> 00:16:30.260 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, if this year Baal gives us no rain,

00:16:31.302 --> 00:16:33.763 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we will certainly know why.

00:16:35.557 --> 00:16:40.562 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What the boy did today was blasphemous.

00:16:42.438 --> 00:16:44.440 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What do you expect?

00:16:46.067 --> 00:16:48.444 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He spent all of his time with my father.

00:16:48.444 --> 00:16:50.780 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He must be punished!

00:16:50.780 --> 00:16:54.200 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Hold your tongue if you want to keep it!

00:16:55.410 --> 00:16:59.289 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You may be a priest of Baal, but do not forget who’s king here!

00:17:01.583 --> 00:17:02.876 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I most certainly will not.

00:17:04.335 --> 00:17:05.587 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Good.

00:17:05.587 --> 00:17:07.589 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Now go!

00:17:07.589 --> 00:17:09.966 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And take that with you.

00:17:10.800 --> 00:17:12.719 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
No.

00:17:12.719 --> 00:17:17.223 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It will remain here for you to reflect upon, my lord the king.

00:17:37.577 --> 00:17:39.704 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
No! Argh!

00:17:47.837 --> 00:17:49.881 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Help! Help!

00:17:51.466 --> 00:17:53.509 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Somebody has murdered the king!

00:18:26.084 --> 00:18:29.963 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Josiah, you’re not alone.

00:18:31.381 --> 00:18:33.633 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah is with you,

00:18:33.633 --> 00:18:37.804 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and so is your cousin Zephaniah.

00:18:54.237 --> 00:18:57.115 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Long live the king!

