Long live the king!

00:19:25.601 --> 00:19:26.728 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Enan.

00:19:28.146 --> 00:19:29.981 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
My lord

00:19:29.981 --> 00:19:32.025 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
is a king.

00:19:33.026 --> 00:19:34.027 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Zephaniah,

00:19:34.986 --> 00:19:37.655 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
prophet of Jehovah, so good to see you too.

00:19:37.655 --> 00:19:40.658 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
My king,

00:19:40.658 --> 00:19:43.745 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I know you must feel so overwhelmed by all this.

00:19:44.746 --> 00:19:47.540 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I will truly miss your father.

00:19:47.540 --> 00:19:49.876 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He was a good, tolerant man

00:19:49.876 --> 00:19:53.087 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
who allowed everyone to worship as they wished.

00:19:54.380 --> 00:19:56.007 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You know,

00:19:56.007 --> 00:20:00.511 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
your father consulted with me regularly

00:20:00.511 --> 00:20:02.764 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
on very important matters.

00:20:04.307 --> 00:20:05.725 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Josiah,

00:20:06.934 --> 00:20:09.353 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
can we still shoot arrows sometimes?

00:20:10.855 --> 00:20:12.273 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Maybe.

00:20:14.400 --> 00:20:16.444 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We’ll leave you, my lord.

00:20:16.444 --> 00:20:20.073 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Again, my sincerest condolences for the loss of your father.

00:20:22.325 --> 00:20:24.702 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I’m here

00:20:24.702 --> 00:20:26.704 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
whenever you need me.

00:20:42.762 --> 00:20:44.972 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
OK. Let’s try again.

00:20:52.522 --> 00:20:54.941 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Keep your hand steady—like this.

00:20:55.942 --> 00:20:59.946 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Remember, don’t focus on the arrow; focus on the target.

00:21:02.031 --> 00:21:03.825 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Like this?

00:21:03.825 --> 00:21:04.826 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Good.

00:21:15.294 --> 00:21:16.963 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You’ve improved.

00:21:19.966 --> 00:21:21.384 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Enan,

00:21:21.384 --> 00:21:23.177 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I’d almost given up on you.

00:21:23.177 --> 00:21:25.179 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We’re almost done.

00:21:25.179 --> 00:21:27.515 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Enan, let’s see who can hit center first.

00:21:28.057 --> 00:21:29.267 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
There’s no contest.

00:21:29.267 --> 00:21:31.018 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You have more time to practice.

00:21:31.018 --> 00:21:35.189 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I have to practice so that I can defeat Jehovah’s enemies.

00:21:35.189 --> 00:21:38.067 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The history of the kings teaches us

00:21:38.067 --> 00:21:40.611 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
much about good and bad.

00:21:40.611 --> 00:21:43.072 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When we carefully study their lives,

00:21:43.072 --> 00:21:44.157 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we learn that—

00:21:44.991 --> 00:21:46.576 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—we need to love Jehovah and hate what is bad.

00:21:48.202 --> 00:21:49.495 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Yes, we know.

00:21:49.495 --> 00:21:50.705 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But why does it matter?

00:21:50.705 --> 00:21:52.123 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Weren’t most kings bad anyway?

00:21:52.123 --> 00:21:53.541 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
That’s true, some were.

00:21:54.667 --> 00:21:57.378 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They didn’t trust in Jehovah,

00:21:57.378 --> 00:21:59.547 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and they didn’t draw close to him.

00:21:59.547 --> 00:22:02.300 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When the king does not search for Jehovah,

00:22:02.300 --> 00:22:05.303 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
everyone suffers, even the good people.

00:22:05.303 --> 00:22:09.599 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
All the more reason to learn from their mistakes.

00:22:12.351 --> 00:22:15.771 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Do you understand what kind of influence a king has?

00:22:17.398 --> 00:22:19.442 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I think so.

00:22:19.442 --> 00:22:21.402 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
My grandfather was a great man—

00:22:21.694 --> 00:22:24.030 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
My father says that King Manasseh

00:22:24.030 --> 00:22:25.656 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
may have been a little brutal,

00:22:25.656 --> 00:22:28.201 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but he was effective, and he was tolerant.

00:22:28.201 --> 00:22:29.911 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He gave the people many freedoms.

00:22:29.911 --> 00:22:32.246 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Enan, having freedom

00:22:32.246 --> 00:22:34.665 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
means having responsibility.

00:22:34.665 --> 00:22:36.459 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The responsibility—

00:22:36.459 --> 00:22:38.085 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Here we go again.

00:22:38.085 --> 00:22:42.548 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The responsibility to choose who we will serve

00:22:42.548 --> 00:22:45.551 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—Jehovah or other gods.

00:22:47.386 --> 00:22:51.182 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
My father says that after the Assyrians released Manasseh,

00:22:51.182 --> 00:22:53.851 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
worshipping only one god weakened him

00:22:53.851 --> 00:22:57.355 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and he started ruling like an old woman.

00:22:57.355 --> 00:22:59.065 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
That’s not true.

00:22:59.065 --> 00:23:01.692 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
My grandfather learned the hard way that Jehovah

00:23:01.692 --> 00:23:03.152 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
is the only true God.

00:23:03.152 --> 00:23:04.153 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And you just insulted him.

00:23:04.153 --> 00:23:06.989 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
My father simply sees the mistakes your grandfather made.

00:23:07.573 --> 00:23:08.908 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Your father should keep his views to himself.

00:23:08.908 --> 00:23:10.409 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
How can you say that?

00:23:10.409 --> 00:23:11.869 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Your father trusted him,

00:23:11.869 --> 00:23:13.329 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and you should too.

00:23:13.329 --> 00:23:15.790 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Besides, you can be loyal to Jehovah

00:23:15.790 --> 00:23:19.919 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and to Baal, Malcam, or any other god at the same time.

00:23:19.919 --> 00:23:22.672 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You don’t honestly believe that?

00:23:23.547 --> 00:23:25.091 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I do.

00:23:26.592 --> 00:23:29.262 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Your father keeps confusing people.

00:23:30.137 --> 00:23:32.974 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So are you telling me I should disrespect him?

00:23:32.974 --> 00:23:35.434 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What about the proverb that says:

00:23:35.434 --> 00:23:37.853 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Listen to your father who caused your birth”?

00:23:37.853 --> 00:23:40.898 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Enan, we must respect our parents.

00:23:40.898 --> 00:23:44.318 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But all of us, including our parents,

00:23:44.318 --> 00:23:46.320 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
owe our lives to Jehovah.

00:23:46.320 --> 00:23:48.322 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
If we just go along with our parents

00:23:48.322 --> 00:23:51.242 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in doing something Jehovah hates,

00:23:51.242 --> 00:23:54.537 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
aren’t we honoring them more than Jehovah?

00:23:56.539 --> 00:23:58.582 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He just makes me so mad!

00:23:58.582 --> 00:24:03.379 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“My grandfather was a great man, and you insult him.

00:24:03.379 --> 00:24:06.841 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Zephaniah is a prophet; you must listen to him!”

00:24:06.841 --> 00:24:11.554 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Prophets come and go.

00:24:11.554 --> 00:24:13.931 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He’s not even old enough to be a real prophet.

00:24:13.931 --> 00:24:17.059 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What is he—25 at the most?

00:24:17.059 --> 00:24:19.312 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And why do we only need to worship Jehovah?

00:24:19.312 --> 00:24:21.856 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
People worship lots of gods.

00:24:21.856 --> 00:24:23.566 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Be careful what you say around Josiah.

00:24:23.566 --> 00:24:28.904 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
His over-righteous spirit may one day turn dangerous.

00:24:28.904 --> 00:24:30.990 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You need to help him be more

00:24:30.973 --> 00:24:33.409 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
balanced, reasonable.

00:24:33.409 --> 00:24:35.578 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
How?

00:24:35.578 --> 00:24:39.332 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Zephaniah says he has a spirit like David.

00:24:41.834 --> 00:24:43.836 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Unfaithful David,

00:24:43.836 --> 00:24:47.465 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
who stole another man’s wife.

00:24:51.552 --> 00:24:54.055 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What is it?

00:24:57.516 --> 00:24:58.726 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Talk to me.

00:25:07.735 --> 00:25:10.154 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What if Josiah is right?

00:25:10.154 --> 00:25:12.865 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Right about what?

00:25:14.408 --> 00:25:16.994 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What if there really is only one true God?

00:25:19.080 --> 00:25:24.710 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Son, Josiah doesn’t see the bigger picture.

00:25:26.420 --> 00:25:30.049 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
His-his grandfather did before he weakened.

00:25:32.802 --> 00:25:34.512 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What can I do?

00:25:34.512 --> 00:25:36.514 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Talk to him.

00:25:38.682 --> 00:25:41.352 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Help him to be a good king

00:25:41.352 --> 00:25:43.020 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—tolerant—

00:25:43.020 --> 00:25:44.647 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
like Manasseh was.

00:25:46.065 --> 00:25:48.776 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Here’s what you can tell him.

00:25:54.990 --> 00:25:56.200 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Josiah.

00:25:59.328 --> 00:26:01.455 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I just wanted—

00:26:03.999 --> 00:26:06.377 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I wanted to apologize.

00:26:06.377 --> 00:26:09.296 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I shouldn’t have spoken to you like that yesterday.

00:26:10.172 --> 00:26:11.382 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It’s all right.

00:26:11.382 --> 00:26:12.675 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I forgave you already.

00:26:12.675 --> 00:26:14.009 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I don’t want any problems between us.

00:26:14.009 --> 00:26:16.262 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It’s just,

00:26:16.262 --> 00:26:18.556 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
what if you’re wrong?

00:26:18.556 --> 00:26:21.517 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What if Baal worship is important?

00:26:21.517 --> 00:26:22.852 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Think about it.

00:26:23.769 --> 00:26:26.772 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Baal is the god of the life-giving rains,

00:26:26.772 --> 00:26:31.735 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and your father and grandfather sacrificed on the high places.

00:26:31.735 --> 00:26:34.697 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But what if Baal cuts off the rains

00:26:34.697 --> 00:26:36.907 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
because you don’t?

00:26:36.907 --> 00:26:41.120 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The crops would die, and the people would starve,

00:26:41.120 --> 00:26:44.123 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and then they would revolt against you.

00:26:48.544 --> 00:26:51.547 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I know how you feel about Jehovah.

00:26:52.715 --> 00:26:57.720 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But isn’t it better to offer the other sacrifices too

00:26:58.554 --> 00:27:00.055 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—just in case?

00:27:04.477 --> 00:27:08.314 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Why would I worry about that when it’s only Jehovah

00:27:08.314 --> 00:27:12.151 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
who can control the weather,

00:27:12.151 --> 00:27:14.487 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
not some false rain god?

00:27:19.408 --> 00:27:21.410 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Don’t you remember,

00:27:21.410 --> 00:27:24.497 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
King Solomon wrote: “All the streams”—

00:27:24.497 --> 00:27:26.123 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I know.

00:27:27.708 --> 00:27:32.213 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“All the streams flow into the sea, yet the sea is not full.

00:27:33.547 --> 00:27:36.425 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“To the place from which the streams flow,

00:27:37.009 --> 00:27:40.721 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
there they return so as to flow again.”

00:27:40.721 --> 00:27:42.097 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
That’s right,

00:27:42.097 --> 00:27:45.100 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
just as Jehovah designed.

00:27:45.100 --> 00:27:47.603 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We studied that scroll together.

00:27:47.603 --> 00:27:51.357 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Well, some people say the scrolls have been altered.

00:27:52.691 --> 00:27:54.693 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Maybe the gods are trying to tell us that—

00:27:54.693 --> 00:27:57.321 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Do you remember when we were little,

00:27:57.321 --> 00:27:59.573 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we would play in the fields?

00:28:00.324 --> 00:28:01.534 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Of course.

00:28:02.826 --> 00:28:04.662 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You always wanted to be King Solomon.

00:28:06.080 --> 00:28:09.917 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah gave Solomon wisdom and riches,

00:28:09.917 --> 00:28:13.212 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but do you also remember the end of the story?

00:28:13.212 --> 00:28:17.716 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
His wives inclined his heart to follow other gods.

00:28:17.716 --> 00:28:21.470 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
His heart wasn’t complete with Jehovah like David’s was.

00:28:24.348 --> 00:28:26.350 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I don’t want to make that same mistake.

00:28:41.407 --> 00:28:44.243 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What are you drawing?

00:28:44.243 --> 00:28:46.412 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It’s the temple.

00:28:46.412 --> 00:28:49.081 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
My grandfather told me how beautiful the temple was

00:28:49.081 --> 00:28:51.750 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
when people would worship Jehovah properly.

00:28:55.421 --> 00:28:58.048 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He said it could be that way again.

00:29:04.597 --> 00:29:07.725 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
I’ll tell you what I intend to do as king.

00:29:08.684 --> 00:29:10.769 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You don’t understand!

00:29:10.769 --> 00:29:13.397 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Josiah plans to tear down all the high places!

00:29:16.692 --> 00:29:18.986 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Oh, I understand all right.

00:29:18.986 --> 00:29:22.990 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When his extremist ideas

00:29:22.990 --> 00:29:25.659 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
become the law of the land,

00:29:25.659 --> 00:29:28.954 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
there will no longer be any joy,

00:29:28.954 --> 00:29:33.250 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
no tolerance, no freedom of worship

00:29:33.250 --> 00:29:37.421 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—only narrow-minded rules

00:29:37.421 --> 00:29:40.257 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and oppressed people.

00:29:40.257 --> 00:29:42.509 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Do you understand that?

00:29:45.679 --> 00:29:47.890 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This is not a good sign.

00:30:15.459 --> 00:30:18.295 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah is holy,

00:30:26.011 --> 00:30:30.683 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and you must serve him the way he wants us to

00:30:30.683 --> 00:30:33.102 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—and only that way.

00:30:35.813 --> 00:30:37.231 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
You, my son,

00:30:37.231 --> 00:30:39.525 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
can become a mighty man

00:30:39.525 --> 00:30:41.694 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
with Jehovah’s help

00:30:42.486 --> 00:30:44.488 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and Baal’s.

00:30:45.989 --> 00:30:50.869 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When the king does not search for Jehovah, everyone suffers,

00:30:50.869 --> 00:30:52.871 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
even the good people.

00:30:54.623 --> 00:30:56.625 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What if you’re wrong?

00:30:58.085 --> 00:31:01.588 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Isn’t it better to offer the other sacrifices too

00:31:02.840 --> 00:31:05.008 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—just in case?

00:31:15.811 --> 00:31:17.896 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Serve Jehovah,

00:31:17.896 --> 00:31:19.356 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Josiah.

00:31:20.190 --> 00:31:23.485 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
All other gods

00:31:25.654 --> 00:31:27.656 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
are powerless.

00:31:32.995 --> 00:31:35.038 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
O Jehovah!

